"Oh,
my
dear,
dear
aunt,"
she
rapturously
cried,
"what
delight!
what
felicity!
You
give
me
fresh
life
and
vigour.
Adieu
to
disappointment
and
spleen.
What
are
young
men
to
rocks
and
mountains?
Oh!
what
hours
of
transport
we
shall
spend!
And
when
we
do
return,
it
shall
not
be
like
other
travellers,
without
being
able
to
give
one
accurate
idea
of
anything.
We
will
know
where
we
have
gone
we
will
recollect
what
we
have
seen.
Lakes,
mountains,
and
rivers
shall
not
be
jumbled
together
