They
were
then,
with
no
other
delay
than
his
pointing
out
the
neatness
of
the
entrance,
taken
into
the
house;
and
as
soon
as
they
were
in
the
parlour,
he
welcomed
them
a
second
time,
with
ostentatious
formality
